{
  "texts": [
    "However, to the best of our knowledge, an analogous compensation mechanism has not been explicitly demonstrated for shift-current responses in nonferroelectric 3R-stacked transition-metal dichalcogenides.",
    "FIG. 6.Field dependence of σzzz (ω; EDC) in 3R-stacked MoS2.",
    "Positive and negative static fields modulate the intrinsic response in opposite directions, and a strong suppression appears when the external field compensates the built-in polarity of the stacking.",
    "We have shown that a static out-of-plane electric field provides an effective way to enable and tune shiftcurrent responses in two-dimensional materials.",
    "Using a combined DFT-Wannier-XATU.Optix workflow [65], we demonstrated how the field breaks inversion in the 2H bilayer and activates a strong second-order response that grows linearly at small static fields and saturates at larger fields."
